      "message": "[🔴 Critical] Line 96: When a retry is already scheduled, later `onPeerOnline()` calls for the same key are dropped entirely, including a potentially different `retryOnTimeout` value. If the first coalesced notification used `retryOnTimeout \u003d\u003d false` and a later one requires timeout retries, the deferred pass will run with the weaker behavior and may leave timed-out messages unsent. Store/update the pending retry parameters, or at minimum OR the flag for an existing timer so the coalesced retry preserves the strongest requested behavior.\n```suggestion\n// Example shape: keep pending retry state per key and update it here.\npendingRetryOnTimeout_[key] \u003d pendingRetryOnTimeout_[key] || retryOnTimeout;\n```",
